Based on the results in Table 4, the production cost (
P c
) increases linearly as the parameter varies from –15% to +15%, leading to a corresponding rise in total cost. The holding cost (
H c
) also shows a linear increase over the same range; however, its impact on the total cost is twofold—between –15% and –5% the total cost decreases, while from +5% to +15% it rises linearly. Similarly, the backorder cost grows linearly across the –15% to +15% interval, which in turn elevates the total cost. As illustrated in Figure 3, the rework cost follows the same pattern, increasing linearly with parameter variation, thereby causing the total cost to increase accordingly.
